Perfect — if you are focusing on **Frontend only**, your goal is different from backend developers.

You should design the frontend so that **it can connect to any backend later**, but you **don't implement the backend**. Instead you **mock the API**.

This is actually **how many frontend developers work in companies**.

So your architecture should be:

```text
UI Components
     ↓
API Service Layer
     ↓
Mock Data / Mock API
```

Later the backend team replaces the mock.

