# 3️⃣ Modify `handleSend`

Change your function to call the API.

```ts
const handleSend = async () => {

  if (!input) return

  const userMessage: Message = {
    role: "user",
    text: input
  }

  setMessages(prev => [...prev, userMessage])
  setInput("")
  setIsTyping(true)

  const aiReply = await sendMessage(input)

  const aiMessage: Message = {
    role: "ai",
    text: aiReply
  }

  setMessages(prev => [...prev, aiMessage])

  setIsTyping(false)
}
```

Now your frontend behaves **exactly like it is calling a real backend**.

